main event: On September 30, 1963, a witness in Murfreesboro, Tennessee observed a circular white light moving slowly east to west before jumping abruptly to another position.
interesting points: The object was reported to move slowly before making an abrupt jump in position., The weather conditions at the time were clear., The sighting was noted in a Project Blue Book record., The object was classified as unidentified., Prior sightings in the area included various shaped objects and lights.
witness description: a private citizen residing in Murfreesboro
